Mac Visual Studio Code shortcuts

- Command + P: Quick Open
- Command + Shift + P: Show All Commands
- Command + Shift + O: Go to Symbol
- Command + Shift + M: Show Problems
- Command + Shift + D: Open Run and Debug
- Command + B: Toggle Sidebar
- Command + J: Toggle Panel
- Command + `: Toggle Integrated Terminal
- Command + K, Command + S: Keyboard Shortcuts
- Command + K, Command + X: Trim Trailing Whitespace
- Command + /: Toggle Line Comment
- Option + Shift + A: Toggle Block Comment
- Shift + Option + F: Format Document
- Command + Shift + K: Delete Line
- Command + Enter: Insert Line Below
- Command + Shift + Enter: Insert Line Above
- Option + Up / Option + Down: Move Line Up/Down
- Shift + Option + Up / Shift + Option + Down: Copy Line Up/Down
- Command + D: Add Selection to Next Find Match
- Command + L: Select Line
- Command + F: Find
- Command + Option + F: Replace in Files
- Command + Shift + \: Jump to Matching Bracket
- Command + K, Command + Z: Toggle Zen Mode
- Command + W: Close Editor
- Command + Shift + T: Reopen Closed Editor
- Command + N: New File
- Command + S: Save File
- Command + Option + S: Save All
- Command + Shift + E: Show Explorer
- Command + Shift + F: Find in Files
- Command + Shift + H: Replace in Files
- Command + K, Command + 0: Focus into Editor Group 0

JavaScript-specific shortcuts

- F12: Go to Definition
- Option + F12: Peek Definition
- Command + .: Quick Fix
- Command + K, Command + I: Show Hover
- Command + K, Command + M: Change Language Mode
- Command + Shift + R: Rename Symbol
- Option + Click: Multi-cursor
- Command + Shift + `: Create New Integrated Terminal
- Command + K, Command + U: Change All Occurrences to Uppercase
- Command + K, Command + L: Change All Occurrences to Lowercase
- Option + `: Show Parameter Hints
- Command + Shift + C: Open New Command Prompt/Terminal
- Command + K, Command + 8: Toggle Problems Panel
- Command + K, Command + /: Toggle Line Comment for selected JS code
